definitions.820-01958: What is 820-01958? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-01958</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> No S3
threads.message:
Board has liquid damage,
I had to route a jumper wire in the <CHIP>U7700</CHIP> area on the <SIGNAL>PPBUS_HS_CPU</SIGNAL> rail which is at 12.6v.
I get 3.2v on <SIGNAL>P1V8PRIM_EN</SIGNAL>. Isn't this supposed to be 1.8v?
The LED light is in what appears to be a white color or possibly blue. 
I have nothing on <SIGNAL>PVDDQ_EN</SIGNAL>, 
.290v on <SIGNAL>PP1V8_S3_FET_R</SIGNAL>.
This board has me confused, what should I do next?

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-01958</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> No S3
threads.message:
"I get 3.2v on <SIGNAL>P1V8PRIM_EN</SIGNAL>. Isn't this supposed to be 1.8v?"
Don't confuse enable signal with the output power rail.

Inspect J6100 and audio flex/board for corrosion; remove it from chassis.
